<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-10-0972 </DOCNO><TEXT>The invention provides a device for detecting, counting or otherwise measuringnuclear radiation. The device comprises a mass of discrete diamond particles,each having a low nitrogen content, held against movement between a pairof plates. The device is arranged to expose the particles to the radiation.Preferably, the diamond particles have a nitrogen content not exceeding100 ppm, and a size between 0,1 and 1 mm.</TEXT></DOC>